  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. If caught, a person may face:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Possible felony charges\n- Prison sentences (typically 2-20 years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Professional consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential business restrictions\n\n4. Additional potential outcomes\n- Mandatory financial reporting requirements\n- Probation\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like the amount of money involved, jurisdiction, previous criminal history, and specific circumstances of the case.",
